The 'Wings' logo and Zoom Air branding highlight the look in Court Purple and Hot Punch, while underfoot, the Zoom Air unit itself is housed in the contrasting white midsole.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High OG A Ma Maniére (PS)
description: The A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 1 High OG PS 'Airness' is made for kids and showcases the Atlanta boutique's updated take on the iconic silhouette. The upper has textured ivory-colored suede with contrasting burgundy accents on the snakeskin-embossed Swoosh and collar. The latter hue is seen again on the woven Nike tongue tag and the retro Wings logo imprinted on the lateral collar. 'A Ma Maniére' script is on the heel overlay. It's built on a cupsole with off-white sidewalls and a burgundy rubber outsole.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE Utility Canvas White Black Gym Red (W)

description: The Air Jordan 1-inspired look of the Air Jordan 1 Centre Court emerges with a subdued colorway on the Air Jordan 1 Centre Court 'Cyber Monday.' The shoe's upper is built with tumbled leather, finished entirely in black and accented by a stylized 'Wings' logo that wraps around the heel. The heel patch itself includes standard 'Wings' branding, while underfoot, Air in the heel of the contrasting white midsole provides cushioning, aided by the Zoom Air in the sockliner.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Defiant White Black Gym Red
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Defiant' brings a deconstructed look to Michael Jordan's first signature shoe. The upper is built with a tumbled leather base in black and white, accented by Gym Red on the stitched lateral-side Swoosh outline. More Gym Red appears on the contrast stitching throughout, while the medial side sports a Tour Yellow Swoosh. Underfoot, the classic Air midsole gives way to an outsole with a pivot-point traction pattern.

First published in 1991, the Air Jordan 6 'Maroon' was the only OG color that never saw a retro release. Nike resurrected this classic in 2015, when the retro was released as part of a huge Holiday drop. The design features branding details including the Jumpman logo on the rubber tongue and lace overlay of the shoe, as well as OG elements on the heel like the Nike Air branding and transparent, translucent outsole.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE White Laser Orange Lucky Green (GS)
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid GS 'Lucky Green Laser Orange' is a grade-school shoe with a vibrant color-blocked look. The shoe's upper is built with a white leather base, overlaid by black leather on the forefoot, eyestay and Swoosh, with Laser Orange and Lucky Green suede on the heel and collar. Underfoot, the midsole houses Air for cushioning, giving way to a final hit of Lucky Green on the concentric outsole.

Made for older kids with a fiery colorway is the Air Jordan 9 Retro GS 'Chile Red.' The crimson textile upper is secured with speed lacing with decorative stitching and overlaid with tonal patent leather throughout the collar, mudguard, and heel with an embroidered 23 and a Jumpman logo superimposed on a globe. It's built on a color-matched foam midsole with a durable black rubber outsole.

shoeName: Jordan x Union Socks Sport Gold/Sunset/Habanero Red
Jordan 1 Mid SE Craft Inside Out White Grey (GS)
Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Sail (W)

description: The Air Jordan 12 Utility GS 'Grind' is a grade-school shoe with a sustainable construction. The shoe's upper is built with tumbled leather, finished in black and sporting stitched detailing throughout. Tonal nubuck further supports the fit, while the midfoot and branding highlight the design in Bright Crimson. A heel pull-loop is included for easy on and off, while underfoot, full-length Zoom Air offers cushioning. Three percent Nike Grind is incorporated on the rubber outsole, which provides traction.

shoeName: Jordan 9 Retro Boot NRG Black Gum
description: The Air Jordan 9 Retro Boot NRG 'Black Gum' features a black suede upper with a black leather mudguard. Finished with a water-resistant coating, the boot-like construction also comes with metal eyelets, a gusseted tongue and a rugged gum rubber outsole. The Air Jordan 9 was the first Air Jordan sneaker released after MJ retired from the NBA in 1994.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE Union Black Toe

description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro Low Wings 'Class of 2020-21' released as part of Jordan Brand's Wings program in May 2021. Giving the nod to that year's class, the shoe's upper is built with a mix of textile and nubuck, finished in black and highlighted by metallic gold '20' and '21' on the lateral heels of each shoe. The lace-lock sports a tassel design, with the sockliner sporting a diploma seal-style design. Underfoot, a polyurethane midsole is included for cushioning, housing visible Air for cushioning. Shark-tooth detailing at the forefoot further highlights the design, while underfoot, an icy translucent rubber outsole offers traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low SE Smoke Grey Gym Red (GS)

description: The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Dark Concord’ is built with black suede, highlighted by Dark Concord accents on the side Jumpman badge on the side profile and lace loops. Underfoot, Zoom Air cushioning works with a carbon fiber midsole plate to provide cushioning and stability.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High CO Japan Neutral Grey (GS)
description: Bringing back a 2001 colorway that was limited to 2,001 pairs and released exclusively in Japan, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG co.JP GS 'Tokyo' dropped in August 2020. A grade-school shoe, the upper is built with nubuck, finished in Neutral Grey and highlighted by metallic silver on the toe box, Swoosh, heel and collar overlay. 'CO.JP' marks the insole, while underfoot, the white midsole houses Air for cushioning.

Released in March 2021, the Air Jordan 5 Retro GS 'Stealth 2.0' is a follow-up to the 2006 'Stealth' colorway. Built with tumbled leather, the shoe's upper appears in white, with tonal netting on the quarter panel. Hyper Royal marks the inner lining and tongue branding as well as the lace lock, which secures the fit. Underfoot, the usual shark-tooth detailing accents the midsole, which houses visible Air for cushioning, while an icy rubber outsole is included for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 4 Retro SP 30th Anniversary Union Taupe Haze
description: Made with the help of Union LA, the Union LA x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Taupe Haze' celebrates the retailer's 30th anniversary. Drawing on a 2020 reimagining of the silhouette from the two brands, the shoe features inspiration from outdoor gear from the 80s and 90s. As a result, the shoe released as part of the Tent and Trail capsule, outfitted with a neutral finish on the mesh and suede upper, highlighted by Roma Green on the lower eyelets and heel patch. Blue Fury instead accents the collar lining and stitched fold-down tongue, which is joined by the translucent TPU wings and yellow 'UN/LA' tag in keeping in line with its predecessor. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning, with a rubber outsole offering traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Zoom Zen Green
description: The Air Jordan 1 High Zoom 'Zen Green' sports a vibrant contrasting look on its classic basketball build. The shoe's upper emerges with a hairy suede base in green, overlaid by black leather and accented by prominent stitching around the quarter panel. Underfoot, the midsole houses Zoom Air in place of the usual Nike Air, while the translucent outsole sports a vibrant finish.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Black Gym Red
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Gym Red' remixes an OG colorway with this June 2019 release. The shoe's leather construction appears in a familiar mix of black, white and Gym Red, with the latter color on the collar and Swoosh branding. Perforations on the toe box provide breathability, while underfoot, a Sail midsole provides Air cushioning. The black outsole sports a concentric pattern for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT London
Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT To My First Coach

description: The Air Jordan 11 Retro PS 'Jubilee' released to celebrate 25 years of the silhouette. A preschool shoe, the upper emerges with a ballistic mesh construction, finished in black and overlaid by tonal patent leather along the mudguard. Metallic silver branding gives the nod to the silver anniversary, while underfoot, a white phylon midsole with Air provides cushioning and contrast. A milky white rubber outsole is included for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 12 Low SE Super Bowl LV
description: Releasing in February 2021 to celebrate the NFL's season finale, the Air Jordan 12 Retro Low SE ‘Super Bowl’ emerges with a festive colorway. Built with black textile, the shoe's upper is highlighted by a multicolor confetti print on the collar lining and inside of the tongue. The signature basketball-textured mudguard appears in Varsity Red, while the midfoot overlay and molded eyelets accent the look in metallic gold. The heel patch appears in a Tamba Bay Buccaneers mix of red and orange as a nod to that year's host city.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE White Black Royal (GS)

description: Dropped in October 2019, the Nike Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS 'Shattered Backboard 3.0' pays homage to the uniform Michael Jordan wore when he shattered the backboard glass during a 1985 Nike exhibition basketball game in Italy. The upper is informed by black and orange patent leather with a textured finish. An embossed Wings logo and Swooshes brand the design. The pale rubber cupsole nods to the shoe's heritage.

Featuring a classic Jordan Brand colorway, the Wmns Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Siren Red' highlights its branding. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears in black, highlighted by Siren Red on the tongue, collar and Swoosh branding, with the color also making its way to the collar. Perforations on the toe box provide breathability, while underfoot, a white Air midsole provides cushioning and contrast, giving way to a black concentric rubber outsole for traction.

A women's shoe, the Wmns Air Jordan 11 Retro Low 'Concord' features a Concord finish on its signature patent leather mudguard. The upper otherwise emerges in white ballistic mesh, supported by webbing eyelets and leather on the heel patch. Underfoot, the Air midsole gives way to an icy blue translucent outsole for traction.

Debuted by Michael Jordan during ESPN's The Last Dance, the Air Jordan 1 Centre Court 'White on White' is the debut colorway of the silhouette. Drawing from tennis shoes, the upper features a white leather construction, with tonal stitched detailing highlighting the heel. The grey suede heel patch includes a debossed 'Wings' logo, while underfoot, Air Jordan 1 tooling supports the fit.

Jordan Brand meshed luxe materials with functional design to create the Jordan 3 Retro SE Animal Pack Fur, now available on StockX. While the first Jordan 3 SE Animal Instinct featured faux fur inspired by Zebras and Giraffes, this release delivers a cold-blooded approach, primarily using reptilian-inspired materials throughout the upper.

The Jordan 3 Retro Animal Instinct 2.0 is comprised of a black croc-textured leather upper with snake and ostrich inspired overlays. Green, yellow, red, and grey detailing prevalent throughout the silhouette. A red Jumpman logo paired with a white sole and yellow heel tabs completes the design. These sneakers released in June of 2020 for $225.

A grade-school shoe, the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Flint' 2020 brings back an OG colorway from 1998. True to its predecessor, the shoe includes reflective detailing on its signature textile overlays, while the rest of the upper appears in white and Flint Grey. A Carolina Blue Jumpman accents the tongue, while underfoot, the panther's paw midsole provides cushioning via Air.

Long before his clutch shooting made him an NBA legend, Michael Jordan sank the game-winning jumper to clinch the 1982 NCAA title for the University of North Carolina. The Air Jordan 11 Retro 'Win Like ’82’ celebrates that championship season with a Tar Heels-inspired colorway that is more subtle than many of its similar counterparts. The white ballistic mesh upper is complemented by a patent leather mudguard in Midnight Navy, while UNC-style light blue marks the Jumpman branding and midsole plate underfoot.

Released in May 2019, the Air Jordan 4 Retro OG GS 'Bred' 2019 pays tribute to the 30th anniversary of the Air Jordan 3. Emerging in the OG colorway that Michael Jordan wore when he hit 'The Shot' in the 1989 playoffs, the shoe's black nubuck upper includes tonal mesh vents, complemented by Cement Grey on the eyelets and lining. Fire Red accents emerge on the tongue branding and outsole, while the midsole houses visible Air in the heel of this grade-school shoe.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid White Laser Orange Deep Royal Blue (GS)

description: Giving the nod to Spike Lee's Do the Right Thing, the Wmns Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Do The Right Thing' features a look inspired by one of the movie's more notable scenes. Modeled after the Air Jordan 4 'White Cement' worn by Buggin' Out, the shoe also draws from the character's custom lacing job. The usual tooling includes visible Air underfoot.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'He Got Game' 2018 features the colorway famously worn by Denzel Washington in He Got Game. The black upper with white quilted overlays is accented by True Red on the outsole and branding, with the signature hologram logo to faithfully recreate the look. Air in the midsole cushions the throwback design.

The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low 'UNC' features a colorway modeled after Michael Jordan's alma mater. The University of North Carolina look is created through a white mesh upper and a University Blue patent leather overlay that covers the base of the shoe. The carbon fiber shank plate features more University Blue, as do the outsole inserts on the translucent outsole.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro SE GS 'Defining Moments' 2020 is a grade-school iteration of a shoe that originally released as part of a two-pack in 2006. Faithful to the original look, the shoe's upper is built with black nubuck, accented by hits of metallic gold throughout. Underfoot, the midsole houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole with translucent sections.

The Air Jordan 11 Retro ‘Platinum Tint’ ditches the one detail most commonly associated with the classic silhouette—its shiny patent leather overlay. Instead, the mid top takes on a nubuck and ballistic mesh construction, finished entirely in subtle Platinum Tint. Contrasting color appears via University Red detailing on the tongue and Jumpman on the lateral heel.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low SE Mighty Swooshers Pink (W)
Jordan 1 Mid SE White Pine Green Smoke Grey (PS)
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE PS 'Grey Pine Green' made in kid sizes features a neutral palette with lush pops of color. The white leather upper is paired with grey suede overlays and accented with a contrasting green leather Swoosh which reappears on the padded collar, rubber outsole, and various branding elements. Included is polished metallic lace jewels and a retro Wings logo debossed on the lateral ankle.

shoeName: Jordan MA2 Luka Doncic Cosmic Deception
Jordan 1 Mid SE White Pine Green (TD)
Jordan 1 Low SE Light Iron Ore (W)
Jordan x Union Socks Equator Blue/Brigade Blue/Habanero Red
Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Aleali May Califia (W)
description: Made with the help of the Los Angeles model and stylist, the Aleali May x Wmns Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort 'Califia' released as part of a larger collection. Drawing from May's time on her high school drill team, the shoe's upper is built with a leather base finished in Hyper Royal and Pine Green, with satin on the collar and Swoosh. Chenille marks the signature 'Wings' branding, while May's signature emerges on the left heel and the lace keeper includes an 'A' logo. Underfoot, top-loaded Zoom Air in the rubber cupsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE Black Dark Beetroot (W)
description: The Wmns Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Gold Pendants' sports elevated accents on its signature design. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears in a mix of black, white and Dark Beetroot, with perforations on the toe box for breathability. A gold Jumpman pendant and matching jewels highlight the look, sporting '1985' and 'Women.' The woven tongue tag deviates from the look with a blue Jumpman, while underfoot, the Air midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low PRM Smoke Grey Elephant

description: Bringing to mind the 'Shattered Backboard,' the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Starfish' features vibrant accents. The shoe's tumbled leather upper appears in white, underlaid by orange suede. A hologram logo stands out on the lateral side, while underfoot, the panther's-paw tooling contrasts the look in black, housing Air for cushioning. A herringbone outsole is included for traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Golf 'Masters Tournament' debuted at the 2021 Masters, where it was worn by Bubba Watson. Sporting accents drawn from the tournament's signature colors, the shoe's upper is built with a white leather base, highlighted by green molded eyelets, with further green on the tongue tag and heel. The textile-lined tongue sports a yellow finish on the interior side, while underfoot, visible Air provides cushioning, with removable spikes on the outsole for traction.

Featuring a subdued colorway, the Air Jordan 4 Retro PS 'White Oreo' is a preschool iteration of the shoe. The retro basketball design emerges with a white leather build on the upper, complemented by Tech Grey on the eyelets and inner lining, matched by the speckled foam midsole. The usual mesh inserts mark the quarter panel and vamp, while underfoot, the look forgoes visible Air in the heel, with a rubber outsole included for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 4 Retro Where the Wild Things Are (TD)
description: Bringing a winterized version to the classic silhouette is the Air Jordan 4 TD 'Wild Things.' The upper is made of tan leather with plush fleece construction on the collar and tongue. Individually colored eyelets are finished in neon green, pink, blue, and red, with blue and red hues repeated on the sneaker's mismatched wings. Jumpman branding decorates the tongue and dark beige heel panel. The shoe is built on a soft foam midsole, reinforced with grippy gum rubber under the forefoot and heel.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Metallic Pack - Court Purple' released as part of the three-shoe Metallic Pack. Built with white leather, the upper includes tonal mesh on the quarter panel and vamp. The look is highlighted by metallic Court Purple on the eyelets, while more Court Purple marks the branding, tongue and Max Air unit in the heel.

The Air Jordan 4 Golf 'White Cement' brings the iconic basketball silhouette to the links. Featuring an OG colorway from 1989, the shoe's upper is built with white leather, highlighted by cement detailing on the quarter panel wings, heel overlay and midsole. The midsole itself houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning, giving way to a full-length outsole plate with seven removable spikes for traction on the course.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low Green Glow Violet Shock (GS)
Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Gold Laser

description:
This Off-White x Jordan T-shirt in black was released on November 12th, 2021, alongside the pair's collaborative Jordan 2 sneaker.

This release included eight new Off-White x Jordan apparel items, making it the largest collaborative collection from the pair in 2021. This particular t-shirt features collaborative Off-White and Jordan logos on both the front and back of the shirt.

The black Off-White x Jordan T-shirt was released on November 12th, 2021, at the retail price of $100.

Featuring the same color-blocking as the Air Jordan 1 'Gold Toe,' the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS 'Silver Toe' is a preschool shoe. Rather than gold patent leather, the shoe's upper is highlighted by a crinkled silver finish on the toe box, heel and collar. Otherwise built with white and black leather, the upper is cushioned underfoot by a rubber cupsole, which incorporates an EVA wedge for cushioning.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High CO Japan Midnight Navy (GS)
description: Releasing in November 2020, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High co.JP GS 'Midnight Navy' 2020 brings back a Japan-exclusive colorway from 2001. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears in a mix of white and Midnight Navy, with metallic silver highlighting the Swoosh branding and 'Wings' logo. Rather than a Jumpman, the tongue includes embroidered Nike branding, while underfoot, Air in the midsole provides cushioning.

The 2016 edition of the Air Jordan 3 Retro OG ‘True Blue’ brings back one of the silhouette’s OG colorways from 1988. This remastered edition of the iconic mid-top is true to the original, highlighted by a white leather upper with True Blue hits on the eyelets, collar lining and Nike Air branding at the heel. Elephant print detailing and a red Jumpman logo hit on the tongue make up the finishing touches.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Black Crimson Tint
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Crimson Tint' features an elevated construction to go with its vibrant colorway. The shoe's upper sports black tumbled leather at the quarter panel, heel and collar, contrasted by Crimson Tint full-grain leather on the perforated toe box, Swoosh, heel and collar overlay. A black nylon tongue maintains the heritage construction, while the white Air midsole provides the only deviation from the two-tone look.

A grade-school shoe, the Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Reverse Flu Game' takes the iconic Jordan colorway and flips its color-blocking. The shoe's upper is built with suede, finished in Varsity Red and contrasted by a basketball-textured overlay in black. A carbon fiber shank supports the fit, while underfoot, the midsole includes Air in the heel in place of the usual full-length Zoom Air.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Black Monarch

description: Adapted for the links, the Air Jordan 5 Low Golf 'Wolf Grey' largely maintains its classic construction. The shoe's upper is built with leather, finished in grey and sporting the usual netting on the quarter panel. Molded eyelets support the lacing system, while the silver tongue sports reflective detailing. Underfoot, the midsole includes the usual shark-tooth detailing, with visible Air in the heel offering cushioning. Removable spikes on the outsole provide traction.

The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low GS 'Concord-Bred' is a grade-school hybrid look. Drawing from two iconic OG colorways, the shoe's leather upper appears in white, overlaid by black patent leather and modeled after the 'Concord.' Underfoot, a white Air midsole and True Red rubber outsole are taken from the 'Bred.'

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Rookie of the Year
description: In 1985, after starting his career with a remarkable point per game average, Michael Jordan won the NBA's Rookie of the Year Award. To celebrate, Jordan Brand released the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Rookie of the Year.' The high top features a white-based leather cap with breathability finger box perforations and mudguard, knee, eyestay, and heel overlays of Gold Harvest leather. Hidden on the inside of each upper strap are callouts to the exceptional rookie season of MJ. On the inside of one strap can be discovered ' 1984-85 R.O.Y. 2313 POINTS 28.2 PPG ' and on the other a quote from Jordan.

shoeName: Jordan 4 Retro Golf Black Cat Pony Hair

description: The Air Jordan 12 Utility TD 'Grind' is a sustainable toddlers' shoe. Appearing in black, the shoe's upper is built with tumbled leather, overlaid by tonal nubuck and sporting stitched detailing throughout. A heel pull-loop is included for easy on and off, while the tongue adds Bright Crimson Jumpman branding to highlight the design. Underfoot, a foam midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a 3% Nike Grind rubber outsole, which sports a speckled finish and provides traction.

A PE colorway made exclusively for Luka Doncic, the Luka Doncic x Air Jordan 36 'Slovenia' released in Asia, Latin America and Europe. The shoe's leno-weave upper is bolstered by synthetic overlays, highlighted by a TPU ribbon that wraps around the throat and heel. The tongue sports a pull-loop for easy on and off, attached to a lace cover that draws from the Air Jordan 6. Underfoot, the Zoom Air strobel stitched directly to the upper is further supported by stacked Zoom Air in the forefoot to provide cushioning, with a midfoot shank included for stability. A herringbone rubber outsole offers traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High OG A Ma Maniére (TD)
description: The A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 1 High OG TD 'Airness' is a shoe designed with the Atlanta-based boutique. The classic silhouette with a luxe makeover features a textured ivory suede upper lined in quilted burgundy textile and accented with burgundy snakeskin detailing on the Swoosh and high-cut collar. Matching colored branding elements include a woven Nike tongue tag, a retro Wings logo stamped on the lateral collar, and 'A Ma Maniére' script on the heel overlay. It's built on a rubber cupsole with vintage off-white sidewalls and a burgundy rubber outsole.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Lemon Twist (W)

description: The Air Jordan 11 Retro 'Cap and Gown' was finally released to the public in 2018, as it was previously a sample from the Air Jordan Blackout Collection in 2011. The name relates to its official look, intended for occasions like graduation ceremonies — its laces are even influenced by graduation cords. The all-black model features on top of an icy blue outsole a patent leather and premium nubuck upper.

Releasing in 2013, the Air Jordan 11 Retro 'Gamma Blue' was a holiday release. Built with a mix of ballistic mesh and patent leather, the shoe's upper appears in black, with Gamma Blue highlighting the Jumpman on the lateral heel. The heel patch and lace bed instead add Varsity Maize to the look, while underfoot, full-length Air in the tonal phylon midsole provides cushioning. A carbon-fiber spring plate offers stability, with a translucent rubber outsole sporting herringbone pods to offer traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE Fearless Maison Chateau Rouge
description: The Maison Chateau Rouge x Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Fearless' showcases a unique blend of debossed patterns and materials, courtesy of the Parisian lifestyle brand. The sneaker’s distinctive color blocking is highlighted by cinnamon accents on an upper finished in pale blue and vanilla hues. Red hand-stitched detailing on the tongue and heel gives the nod to African-inspired basketry and folk art.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Phantom Gym Red
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Phantom' gets its unique look from the use of contrast stitching. The shoe's Sail leather upper sports prominent black and University Red stitching throughout its classic construction, supported by a padded collar and nylon tongue. More University Red emerges on the ankle, while underfoot, the midsole houses Air for cushioning. A concentric outsole pattern provides traction.

The 2017 edition of the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Bred' brings back the classic OG colorway from 1998. This reissue is faithful to the original, featuring 3M reflective mesh overlays atop an upper built with a combination of black tumbled leather and red synthetic suede. Additional hits of True Red appear on the midsole and Jumpman logo embroidered on the tongue.

The Jordan 8 ' Aqua ' was released in 1993 as one of three OG colorways. At the All-Star game in 1993, where Jordan dropped 30 points, the sneaker made its first and only appearance on court. Before its release on Black Friday as part of Jordan's 2015 Holiday Collection, the ' Aqua ' was only retro'd in 2007. The sneaker includes premium materials and authentic details as part of the Nike's ' Remastered ' program.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS 'Lucky Green' is a preschool shoe that draws from Michael Jordan's 63-point performance in a 1986 playoff game against Boston. The shoe's upper is built entirely with leather, finished in white and overlaid by Lucky Green. Red marks the 'Wings' logo, while black Swoosh branding contrasts the side wall. The sockliner includes a parquet floor print inspired by the old Boston Garden, with Air in the midsole underfoot providing cushioning.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro Low Light Iron Ore Siren Red (W)
description: Dressing the classic silhouette in contrasting hues is the women's Air Jordan 1 Low 'Light Iron Ore Siren Red.' It features a leather upper with a bright red base with grey overlays and a signature Swoosh in black. Matching black accents on the Jumpman icon on the tongue and a stitched Wings logo on the heel overlay. The low-top is built on a durable rubber cupsole with an Air-sole heel unit in a lightweight polyurethane wedge.

The Air Jordan 1 Low GS 'Gym Red' is a grade-school shoe with a two-tone look. Built with white leather, the upper is overlaid by Gym Red on the toe, eyestay, heel and collar, matched by the Swoosh. Tonal 'Wings' branding is worked into the heel, while underfoot, the concentric outsole sports further Gym Red.

The Air Jordan 36 First Light boasts a heavy-duty jacquard Leno-Weave upper reinforced with a TPU ribbon that surrounds the collar. A full-length Zoom Air Strobel unit stacked atop a Zoom Air unit in the sole provides the ultimate sensation of energy return and responsiveness.

The Air Jordan 36 First Light released in September of 2021 and retailed for $185.

The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low 'Navy Snakeskin' 2019 is a faithful retro of the 2000 OG. The shoe's defining feature is the mudguard, which replaces the usual patent leather with a navy snakeskin print. The upper is also built with leather instead of mesh, while the Air midsole gives way to an icy translucent outsole.

shoeName: Jordan 11 Retro Low Derek Jeter RE2PECT
description: Reworking the ‘Derek Jeter’ high-top from 2017 into a low-top style, the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low 'RE2PECT' sports a Yankees-inspired colorway of Binary Blue and Sail, and was originally released to 5 winners as part of a free raffle. Its suede upper sits above a translucent outsole and an embroidered ‘2’—Jeter’s number—appears on the back heel.

The Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'Bordeaux' is a grade-school shoe. A collaboration between Paris Saint-Germain and Jordan Brand, the shoe's upper is built with a white leather base, with mesh netting at the quarter panel and vamp providing breathability. Black and Bordeaux add color to the look, while a 'Paname' flag emerges on the forefoot. The heel includes a PSG Jumpman logo, while 'Ici c'est Paris' on the sockliner completes the collaborative look.

In 1991, the Air Jordan 6 'Infrared' released among five original colorways. Retro releases dropped to commemorate the anniversary of the initial release date of the shoe in 2000, 2010 and 2014. The design features an all-black perforated upper nubuck leather with Infrared accents and a return to the reflective upper underlay, a detail that has not been seen since the initial launch of the shoe.

The Wmns Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Tech Chrome' brings a subdued look to the silhouette known for being Michael Jordan's first championship shoe. The shoe's upper is built with suede, finished in black and overlaid by Light Smoke Grey. The forefoot is highlighted by Chrome underlays, while the usual heel pull-tab appears in semitranslucent TPU. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel provides cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 5 Retro JSP Laney Varsity Royal
description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Laney' features a look inspired by Michael Jordan's high school alma mater. Dressed in the Varsity Royal and Varsity Maize colorway of Emsley A. Laney High, the shoe features a nubuck construction with mesh inserts for breathability. The tongue Jumpman branding is built with chenille, while underfoot, a speckled Light Charcoal midsole houses a visible Air unit in the heel.

The Wmns Air Jordan 1 Mid LX 'Off White Opti Yellow' is an updated iteration of the basketball classic. The shoe's upper is built with suede, finished in off-white and highlighted by die-cut Opti Yellow overlays that create the signature design lines. The Swoosh, tongue tag and 'Wings' logo sport a similar finish, while underfoot, the signature rubber cupsole incorporates Air in the heel for cushioning.

Giving the nod to one of the most influential figures in Michael Jordan's life, the Jordan Series .02 'White University Blue' appears in University of North Carolina colors. Paying tribute to legendary coach Dean Smith, the shoe's lateral quarter panel and red woven tongue tag sport 'Dear Dean.' The right sockliner adds 'Swing for the Fences,' while 'There was Never Any Doubt' appears on the translucent rubber outsole. The upper itself is built with a mix of leather, canvas and suede, with the latter in University Blue.

Giving the nod to one of Micheal Jordan's lesser-known nicknames, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Black Cat' emerges with a colorway fit for its moniker. The shoe's upper is built with suede, finished in black and overlaid by mesh, which sports a reflective finish. Rope laces secure the fit, while the usual hologram logo marks the heel. Underfoot, Zoom Air in the forefoot and heel of the phylon midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a herringbone panther's-paw outsole for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Emerald Green (W)

description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro NRG ‘Raptors’ hit stores in 2018, featuring a colorway inspired by the OG Air Jordan 7. Like its predecessor, the mid-top features a black nubuck upper with red and purple accents, the latter hue prominently featured on the shoe’s speckled midsole and Jumpman heel logo. A second Jumpman is embossed on the all-black tongue tag.

The 2015 Air Jordan 11 Retro Low ‘Georgetown’ gives the nod to the Georgetown Hoyas, who fell short in the 1982 NCAA national title game against Michael Jordan and the University of North Carolina. The Grey Mist upper and Midnight Navy patent leather overlay match the Hoyas’ team colors.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High FlyEase Black Gym Red Smoke Grey
description: Bringing the classic Jordan style to athletes of all skill levels is the Air Jordan 1 High FlyEase 'Smoke Grey Gym Red.' It features a black leather upper with a high-cut collar that can be unzipped and folded down for easier accessibility and hook-and-loop closure on the lateral eyestay for a wide opening to get into smoother. Contrasting scarlet accents are on the multiple branding elements, while grey leather is used on the padded collar and perforated toe box. It's built on a rubber cupsole with an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the heel.

Part of a collection between the fashion house and Jordan Brand, the Dior x Air Jordan 1 High released in April 2020. The shoe's Italian leather upper appears in a mix of white and grey, with a Dior Oblique jacquard Swoosh contrasting the side wall. The tongue tag and 'Wings' logo sport co-branding, with further branding revealed by the icy translucent outsole.

The OFF-WHITE x Air Jordan 1 is created by designer Virgil Abloh in the classic Chicago colorway. Some of the half-finished characteristics of the sneaker include an OFF-WHITE zip tie on the collar, a Swoosh linked to the shoe with noticeable blue stitching, 'Air' printed on the midsole. The box is deconstructed as it is turned inward with the inside consisting of a black structure and a gold Jumpman logo, while the outside is plain cardboard with the words 'Jumpman' printed on it. The Virgil OFF-WHITE collection included Air VaporMax, Air Presto, Air Max 90, Blazer, Air Max 97, Hyperdunk 2017, Air Force 1, Zoom Fly, and Chuck Taylor remixed iterations.

The 'Bred' Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG features an updated black and Varsity Red Flyknit top with a white midsole and Varsity Red outsole. The sneaker also features Nike Air branding on the tongue and a Wings logo on the ankle collar, which was released in September 2017.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Gatorade Blue Lagoon
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG G8RD 'Blue Lagoon' dropped in 2018 as part of a larger collaboration with Gatorade, the sports drink responsible for the iconic ‘Be Like Mike’ TV commercial from 1992. The high-top sports a monochromatic bright blue finish, accented by an orange tongue tag and matching orange Gatorade lightning bolt logo at the lateral heel.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Fearless Come Fly With Me

description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Olympic’ dropped in 2016 to coincide with the Rio Summer Olympics. The celebratory design makes use of a white leather upper, complemented by metallic gold accents on the padded tongue and lace locks, as well as the signature shark-tooth detailing on the contrasting black midsole. A final touch of gold appears on the Jumpman logo beneath the translucent outsole.

Originally part of a sample collection at the 2010 World Basketball Festival, the Air Jordan 7 Retro ‘Pantone’ finally saw a general release in 2017. The University of North Carolina colorway features University Blue throughout its nubuck upper, only broken up by hits of white on the heel and branding. The sole unit takes the inverse approach, with an all-white look, including on the signature midsole detailing, broken up by a University Blue Jumpman on the outsole.

colorway: Black/Ember Glow-Barely Volt-Light Soft Pink-Jade Aura
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Glow In The Dark' is a kids'-exclusive shoe. The upper is built with leather, with a black base overlaid by Ember Glow, Barely Volt, Light Soft Pink and Jade Aura, with the Swoosh branding taking on a multicolor stitched construction. Underfoot, Air in the midsole provides cushioning, while the rubber outsole adds a glow-in-the-dark finish to give the shoe its name.

The Wmns Air Jordan 1 Low Slip 'Chicago' released in March 2019, bringing a 2007 sample to retail. The shoe's leather upper is finished in a familiar 'Bred' look, while the laceless construction features a series of tags down the tongue. A 'Wings' logo appears on the heel, while underfoot, the white midsole houses Air for cushioning. A concentric outsole pattern provides the usual traction.

shoeName: Jordan Flight Club 91 Black University Red
Jordan x Union M J FLC Hoodie Sport Gold
silhoutte: Jordan x Union M J FLC
make: Jordan x Union M J FLC

description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro TD 'University Blue' is a toddlers' shoe with a University of North Carolina look. Built with suede, the shoe's upper appears primarily in University Blue, with 'White Cement'-style detailing on the wings, heel and midsole adding to the aesthetic. That foam midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole with a herringbone pattern for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low SE Violet Shock White Black

description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS 'Seafoam' is a preschool shoe with a pastel look. The shoe's upper is built with a white leather base, overlaid by nubuck in Seafoam that complements the design. Healing Orange brings color to the two-tone laces, while perforations on the toe box offer breathability. Underfoot, a two-tone rubber cupsole with a concentric rubber outsole anchors the design.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Cauliflower (W)
Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Canyon Rust (W)

description: The Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Arctic Pink' brings a distressed finish to grade-school sizes. The design emerges throughout the cracked suede upper, with the abstract pattern contrasted by synthetic white leather on the mudguard. The heel pull-loop, molded eyelets, inner lining and tongue branding add a more vibrant pink to the look, while underfoot, the phylon midsole works with a shank plate for cushioning and stability. A herringbone pattern on the outsole offers traction.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Quai 54' 2021 released to celebrate the annual Parisian streetball tournament. The shoe's upper is built with a white leather base, highlighted by University Red on the TPU eyelets and accented by a Quai 54 logo, partially visible through the quarter panel netting. The inner lining and laces add an abstract print to the design, while reflective detailing marks the tongue. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel offers cushioning, giving way to a Quai 54-branded translucent rubber outsole for traction.

The Wmns Air Jordan 14 Retro Low 'Red Lipstick' emerges in a familiar two-tone look inspired by lipstick. The Ferrari-inspired silhouette emerges with a black nubuck construction on the upper, highlighted by Gym Red along the collar, tongue and throat. A tonal quarter panel badge complements the design, while underfoot, the speckled phlyon midsole houses Zoom Air for cushioning, with a silver shank plate for stability. The sockliner sports text in a style that mimicks lipstick, with lipstick-stained tissue paper wrapping the shoe to complete the thematic look.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG TD 'Pollen' is a toddlers' shoe with classic color-blocking and a contrasting look. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears with a black base contrasted by Pollen on the overlays and Swoosh branding, with a black 'Wings' logo in the usual spot on the collar. Underfoot, a white midsole contrasts the design, giving way to a concentric rubber outsole for traction.

Updating the classic silhouette with a subtle palette and unique graphic elements inspired by anime is the Air Jordan 1 Low SE 'Mighty Swooshers.' The leather upper has varying pastel shades of blue with white quarter panels and a matching white forefoot overlay. A glossy finish distinguishes the eyestay and signature Swoosh, while an embroidered Jumpman and Wings logo are featured on the tongue and back heel. It's built on an icy translucent rubber outsole which reveals anime-style artwork.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Noble Red' subtly alters a classic Jordan Brand colorway. Built entirely with leather, the upper emerges in a mix of black and white highlighted by Noble Red on the toe box, collar and branding. Underfoot, a white Air midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a final hit of Noble Red on the concentric outsole.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Black Chile Red

description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro OG PS 'Fire Red' 2020 is a preschool iteration of the shoe. Released in November 2020, the shoe emerges with an OG colorway, built with a white leather base and tonal netting at the quarter panel and vamp. Black provides conrast, while Fire Red highlights the design. Underfoot, the foam midsole provides cushioning, with the usual visible Air in the heel noticeably absent.

Releasing to celebrate the Quai 54 streetball tournament in Paris, the Air Jordan 1 Low 'Quai 54' 2021 dropped in July 2021. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears in white, contrasted by black on the nubuck overlays and Swoosh branding. The inner lining and textile collar add an abstract print to the look, while the heel is marked by a Quai 54 logo. Underfoot, Air in the heel provides cushioning, with a concentric rubber outsole offering traction and highlighting the look in red.

The Air Jordan 1 Low 'UNC' looks to Michael Jordan's college alma mater for its two-tone look. Built with leather, the upper appears with a white base overlaid by University Blue, supported by a padded collar and perforated toe box. Underfoot, the midsole houses Air in the heel for cushioning, with a concentric outsole for traction.

A classic Jordan Brand colorway, the Air Jordan 14 Retro 'Gym Red' features a familiar mix of Chicago Bulls colors. The last shoe that Michael Jordan wore on the court, the upper is built with suede, finished in Gym Red and overlaid by black on the toe. Underfoot, the contrasting white midsole houses Zoom Air and a shank plate for cushioning and stability, giving way to a herringbone outsole.

The Air Jordan 3 Retro PS 'Pine Green' is made for younger kids and adds verdant color-popped accents to the hardwood stalwart that originally launched in 1988. The upper is constructed from smooth black nubuck with signature elephant print overlays at the forefoot and heel. Contrasting hits of Pine Green appear on the eyelets, perforated collar, and the Jumpman icon embroidered on the tongue. On the back heel is a second Jumpman logo while the shoe rests on a two-tone foam midsole with a durable grey rubber outsole.

Released in September 2020, the Air Jordan 14 Retro 'Hyper Royal' features a look with color-blocking modeled after a 1998 OG model. Built with smooth and tumbled leather in white, the tongue and heel sport hits of Hyper Royal, matched underfoot by the detailing on the midsole. A carbon fiber shank plate provides support underfoot.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Fearless Metallic Rose Gold (W)
description: The women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Fearless' updates the iconic silhouette with a glossy dot-textured mesh upper, finished in contrasting black and Metallic Rose Gold hues. Details include a woven Nike Air tongue tag, Jordan Wings logo on the lateral collar and Fearless branding on the custom sockliner. The kicks are anchored by an all-white midsole and outsole.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE Iron Purple Deep Royal (W)
Jordan 1 Retro High Spider-Man Origin Story
description: Inspired by ‘Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse,’ the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Origin features a revised take on the silhouette’s iconic Chicago colorway, worn by the teenage protagonist of the film, Miles Morales. Unique details include a blue and red tongue tag, translucent rubber outsole and tonal reflective dots covering the shoe’s red leather overlays.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE White Black Red Spruce (GS)

description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High Zoom 'Fearless' released as part of a larger collection in December 2019. The shoe's upper appears almost entirely in black, but the design is finished entirely in reflective detailing. Perforations on the tongue and toe box add breathability, while underfoot, the midsole incorporates Zoom Air for cushioning. The icy translucent outsole includes a circular traction pattern and gradient finish.

The 2016 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Flu Game’ brings back the shoe that Michael Jordan wore in Game 5 of the 1997 NBA Finals. Despite suffering flu-like symptoms, MJ would go on to score 38 points in a winning effort that gave the Bulls a 3-2 series edge over the Utah Jazz. This reissue is true to the original, featuring a black leather upper with contrasting Varsity Red on the mudguard and outsole.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Red Suede
description: Featuring a classic Jordan Brand colorway, the Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort 'Gym Red' updates the iconic silhouette. Built with suede, the shoe's upper appears in Gym Red, with a cutout Swoosh and deconstructed collar contrasting the look in black. Underfoot, Zoom Air in the midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a speckled concentric rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High First Class Flight
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'First Class Flight' makes use of a perforated white leather upper with yellow accents on the collar, medial-side Swoosh and rubber outsole. Unique details include Michael Jordan’s signature on the lateral collar and black barcodes on the heel and medial-side ankle flap, the latter referencing Jordan Brand's shipping department while the latter contains MJ's career statistics.

Showcasing a familiar palette rendered in OG-inspired color blocking is the Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Court Purple.' Made for younger kids, it features reflective textile overlays that dominate the upper, constructed from black leather with contrasting violet suede paneling. A matching purple Jumpman decorates the microfiber tongue, while the 13's holographic cat eye shines on the lateral ankle. The mid-top is built on a panther paw outsole with herringbone-traction rubber pods.

After debuting in 2006 to support Hurricane Katrina relief efforts, the Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Hall of Fame' was re-released in 2018 to celebrate both Michael Jordan’s humanitarianism and his induction into the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame. The sneaker boasts a white leather upper, accented by black, Fire Red, cement grey, and elephant print details. The iconic Jumpman logo appears on the heel.

The Air Jordan 1 Low 'Court Purple' brings an elevated look to its low-top construction. Built entirely with leather, the upper's black base is highlighted by Court Purple overlays, with white contrast provided by the Swoosh. Tonal 'Wings' branding is embroidered on the heel, while a nylon tongue adds a retro touch. The midsole houses Air for cushioning.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High '85 'Varsity Red' emerges with a look that essentially flips the iconic 'Banned' colorway. Built with leather, the upper sports a black base overlaid by Varsity Red. A padded nylon tongue supports the fit, while underfoot, a white Air midsole provides cushioning and contrast.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Yellow Toe' emerges with a colorful take on the 'Black Toe' concept. The mid-top is built with a leather base overlaid by suede, finished in a mix of black and Tour Yellow, with white on the quarter panel. Perforations on the toe box provide breathability, while underfoot, an Air midsole provides cushioning. The outsole sports a pivot-point tread as well as a Tour Yellow finish.

shoeName: Jordan 5 Retro Low Golf Black Grape
Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Bayou Boys

description: The Jordan MA2 'Future Beginnings' emerges with a deconstructed look. The shoe's upper is built with textile, overlaid by suede and finished in off-white. The design incorporates exposed stitching, unfinished edges and unconventional logo tags to add to the look, while underfoot, the midsole houses a vibrant Max Air unit in the heel to provide cushioning. A gum rubber outsole offers traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Arctic Orange Black Toe (PS)
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Crimson Tint' is a preschool shoe with a contrasting mix of hues. Built with leather, the shoe's upper sports a white base, contrasted by black and complemented by Crimson Tint, including on the Swoosh and eyestay. An added heel pull-loop is included for easy on and off, while underfoot, the white midsole gives way to a rubber outsole with a concentric pattern for traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Pure Money' 2017 features its signature subdued colorway, with a white leather upper accented by metallic silver eyelets and heel Jumpman branding. 'Pure $' appears inside the heel tab, while visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Royalty' brings elevated accents and an elevated construction to the classic basketball silhouette. Built with suede, the shoe's upper appears in black, overlaid by synthetic leather on the heel and highlighted by metallic gold on the signature eyelets and heel branding. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel of the contrasting polyurethane midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a herringbone rubber outsole for traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'Lemon Venom' is a grade-school shoe with vibrant accents. Built with a white leather base, the upper sports Lemon Venom and Pink Blast, with the latter color notably on the mesh inserts. Underfoot, the white midsole houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning, giving way to a tonal rubber outsole that provides traction.

Giving the nod to the fourth anniversary of the SNKRS app in Europe, the Air Jordan 1 Low 'SNKRS Day' released on August 8, 2021. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears in yellow, overlaid by tan suede and supported by a mesh collar. The Swoosh and forefoot overlay are built with suede, sporting a series of leopard spots to accent the design. The SNKRS anniversary date joins Jumpman branding on the tongue tag, while underfoot, more leopard sports appear through the translucent rubber outsole, which offers traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low Black White Gym Red (W)

description: The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Chicago' 2017 brought the OG 'Chicago' colorway back to the Jordan 13 silhouette. Featuring a white premium leather upper with quilted overlays, Team Red suede brings color to the heel, midfoot and midsole. Black on the Jumpman branding and sole complete a Chicago Bulls look.

The 2015 reissue of the Air Jordan Retro ‘Hare’ celebrates the novel partnership between Michael Jordan and Bugs Bunny, who starred together in a memorable ‘90s ad campaign. The design of the mid-top is true to the original, featuring a light silver nubuck base and white leather overlays, along with contrasting pops of red on the outsole, neoprene tongue and the shoe’s branding elements.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low SB QS Lance Mountain Desert Ore
description: A December 2019 debut, the Nike SB x Air Jordan 1 Low communicates Lance Mountain's influence from his early days with the Bones Brigade. Frequently featuring two different colorways at once, the new AJ1 Low shows off a base Royal and UNC color with a top layer that has a Desert Ore finish designed to wear off and reveal the design beneath. Iconic elements include standout laces, a bicolored tongue badge, and Wings branding on the heel. A rubber cupsole unites the look.

Nike merged three original Air Jordan 1 colorways (Bred, Chicago, and Royal ) into a fresh colorway in 2016, known as the 'Top 3'. With the Wings logo on the ankle and the Nike Air branding on the insole and tongue, the sneaker comes in mismatched' color panels and outsoles while remaining true to the original design. 'Top 3' also refers to Jordan being drafted third overall in the NBA draft.

shoeName: Jordan 5 Retro Low Golf Lucky and Good
description: The Air Jordan 5 Low Golf NRG 'Lucky and Good' updates the classic basketball silhouette for the links. The shoe's upper is built with corduroy in place of leather, finished entirely in Sail. The quarter panel insert remains intact, as does the toggle lacing system. The Starfish inner lining adds color to the look, while Neptune Green emerges on the tongue branding and shark-tooth detailing. Underfoot, the translucent outsoles reveal 'Rather Lucky' and 'Than Good,' while removable spikes provide traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Pale Citron' released to help celebrate the 30th anniversary of the iconic silhouette. The shoe's upper is built white leather, with mesh vents for breathability. Contrasted by black on the lining, heel and eyelets, a unique Bright Crimson graphic emerges on the quarter panel flange and midsole. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning, giving way to a multicolor herringbone outsole for traction.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Chicago' 2015 colorway features full-leather uppers in Bulls team colors. The 'Chicago' was first retroed in 1994 and stayed true to the 1985 design. Further retros were released in 2013 with small changes to the design, and again in 2015 with the original branding details: the Nike Air logo on the tongue and the original clean heel without the Jumpman logo.

One of the initial Air Jordan 1 line colorways, the 'Black Toe' Air Jordan 1 Retro grew in popularity after being featured in several Nike promotional campaigns (including the picture inspired by the Jordan logo itself). Surprisingly, however, Jordan only wore this colorway in a couple of games, improving its popularity.

During the NBA All-Star game, Nike dropped a brand new Air Jordan 6 called the 'Chameleon.' The shoe released alongside a comparable looking Air Jordan 1 and Air Jordan 31. The Air Jordan 6 All-Star 'Chameleon' has an all-black leather upper and a distinctive iridescent color, giving the shoe a color-changing impact depending on the light.

The Air Jordan 1 Centre Court 'Military Blue' reimagines the classic silhouette with unique detailing. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears in white, with a stylized wings logo that wraps around the heel. A blue overlay also wraps around the heel, bringing color to the look, while underfoot, an Air Jordan 1 cupsole with Air in the heel provides cushioning. However, Zoom Air in the sockliner has been added to further cushion the fit.

Featuring a look similar to the 'Black Cat' iteration, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Cap and Gown' stands out with its udpated build. The shoe's monochromatic colorway includes patent leather overlays on its suede base. Underfoot, the panther's paw tooling incorporates Zoom Air for cushioning and a carbon fiber plate for stability. Up top, the signature hologram logo has also been blacked out.

The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Infrared 23’ delivers a revised take on the silhouette’s OG White/Cement colorway from 1988. Like the original, the mid-top makes use of a white leather upper with elephant print overlays at the toe and heel. Updates include Infrared eyelets and added hits of basic black coloring on the tongue, collar, midsole and outsole.

By throwing down a monstrous dunk while wearing an orange, black, and white uniform, Michael Jordan broke a backboard during a Nike Europe tour in 1985. A 2015 Air Jordan 1 'Shattered Backboard' was released to commemorate the moment and uniform. This sneaker maintains the branding of black laces and Nike, but swaps the orange toe box and black around the white toe and tongue.

shoeName: Jordan 7 Retro Reflections of a Champion
description: Part of the Reflections of a Champion pack, the Air Jordan 7 Retro SP 'Reflections Of A Champion' celebrates Michael Jordan's second NBA title. The shoe emerges with 3M reflective detailing throughout its upper construction, accented by black, Cardinal Red and bronze. A heel pull-loop provides easy on and off, while underfoot, an Air midsole provides cushioning. A rubber outsole is included for traction.

The Supreme x Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Desert Camo' dropped alongside white and black colorways of the retro silhouette in October 2015. Featuring a unique desert camo print on a textile upper, the mid-top features a silver reflective tongue and ‘Sup’ branding on the quarter panel. Additional unique details take include ‘94’ on the lateral heel and dual Jumpman and Supreme logo hits on the outsole.

shoeName: Jordan 13 Retro Alternate History of Flight
description: In 2009, Jordan Brand presented the collection History of Flight with iconic silhouettes retro colorways that were never made accessible to the public. The Air Jordan 13 Retro ' History of Flight ' released for the first time in 2017 features a tumbled white leather top with a matching beaded overlay. The sneaker also displays University Red details on collar and tongue lining and outsole traction-forward, black lacing system details, and panther-inspired branding on the hologram logo.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High FlyEase White Cardinal Red

description: With iconic flair, the Air Jordan 1 Mid GS 'Top 3' kids' shoe blends suede and grained leather in a layered four-color palette. The well-known branding emerges with a Jumpman on the tongue and a debossed black Wings logo on the upper lateral side. The toe box, mudguard, and collar appear in the classic 'Bred' colorway. A two-tone sole matches the quarter panel highlighted with a metallic, silver-trimmed Swoosh.

The Jordan ADG 'White Cement' adapts iconic Jordan elements for the links. Inspired by Michael Jordan's passion for golfing, the shoe features a white tumbled leather upper accented by elephant print on the toe and heel, continuing down onto the midsole. The tongue and heel counter sport Fire Red Jumpman branding, while a Zoom Air midsole provides cushioning. A unique outsole tread is included for traction.

Featuring pastel hits, the Jordan Delta 2 'Platinum Tint' is a lifestyle silhouette. Built with suede, the shoe's upper appears in grey, with the suede eyestay adding purple and the heel pull-loop and molded mudguard adding teal. White textile overlays support the fit, while the lateral side sports 'Jordan' branding and the medial side includes an embroidered '23.' Underfoot, a React foam midsole provides cushioning, giving way to an outsole that incorporates durable rubber in high-wear areas to provide traction.

The Paris Saint-Germain x Jordan Mars 270 'Infrared' is a collaboration between the iconic French soccer club and Jordan Brand. The Jordan Mars 270, a hybrid look inspired by Spike Lee's Mars Blackmon, emerges in a mix of Infrared 23, Reflect Silver and black on its tumbled leather and mesh build, accented by PSG branding on the quarter panel flag and heel. Underfoot, the midsole incorporates a bold Max Air unt in the heel, with an icy translucent outsole providing traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low White Lucky Green Black

description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Anthracite' brings a unique construction to the classic basketball silhouette. Built with suede and textile, the shoe's upper appears in Anthracite, contrasted by the eyelets and quarter panel netting. Rather than the tongue, the usual reflective detailing makes its way to the quarter panel, while underfoot, speckled shark-tooth detailing highlights the midsole. Visible Air in the heel is included for cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low To My First Coach

description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS 'Pollen' is a preschool shoe with a contrasting look. The shoe's upper is built with leather, with a black base highlighted by Pollen overlays throughout, including on the Swoosh branding. A lightly padded nylon tongue supports the fit, as does a perforated toe box, while underfoot, a white rubber midsole gives way to a concentric rubber outsole for traction.

Inspired by the OG colorway of the Air Max 95, the Air Jordan 4 Retro LE 'Neon 95' features vibrant accents on its largely neutral costruction. The shoe's upper is built with suede, finished in a greyscale pattern and highlighted by the eyelets, quarter panel netting and heel branding. Underfoot, more Volt marks the Air unit in the heel.

A toddlers' shoe, the Air Jordan 5 Retro TD 'Raging Bull' 2021 released more than a decade after the original colorway, which dropped in 2009 as part of the Defining Moments pack. Built with suede, the shoe's upper appears in Varsity Red, with translucent netting marking the quarter panel. Reflective silver detailing accents the tongue, while underfoot, the black foam midsole forgoes the usual visible Air in the heel, but it maintains the classic shark-tooth detailing.

The Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Court Purple' brings subtly vibrant accents to its classic construction. Built with tumbled leather, the upper features a black base, highlighted by Court Purple on the collar, eyelets and midsole. Elephant print marks the forefoot and heel, while the inner tongue and branding add further color to the look. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

shoeName: Jordan 13 Retro White Obsidian Powder Blue (GS)
description: Available in kid sizes is the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Obsidian.' It updates the classic silhouette in a familiar palette to that of an OG colorway of the Air Jordan 12. The upper has stitched white leather overlays that dominate a blend of navy leather along the forefoot and tonal suede paneling at the midfoot and heel. Branding elements include a powder blue Jumpman embroidered on the tongue and the 13's holographic cat eye on the lateral collar. The feline theme carries on with a panther paw outsole with herringbone-traction rubber pods.

A toddlers' iteration of the shoe, the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low TD 'Legend Blue' features an OG colorway. Built with synthetic leather, the shoe's upper appears in white, with elastic no-tie laces securing the fit. Black contrasts the inner lining, while the tongue Jumpman includes a Legend Blue finish. Underfoot, a foam midsole provides cushioning, giving way to an icy translucent rubber outsole for traction.

Built for kids a bit older, the Air Jordan 1 Low MMD BG 'Multi Grid' updates the sneaker classic with mismatched colors and geometric prints. It features a contrast-colored grid pattern on the collar, toe, and heel panel, with forefoot overlays covered in blue-on-black microdots. The remaining upper is made from white leather with the iconic Swoosh in Bright Mango. An encapsulated Air unit enhances the cushioning properties of the rubber cupsole, with mismatched blue and yellow rubber outsoles. The laces feature the same hues as well.

shoeName: Jordan 4 Retro Where the Wild Things Are (PS)
description: The Air Jordan 4 PS 'Wild Things' are shoes for little kids and made for colder weather. It has fleece on both the padded collar and Jumpman icon embroidered tongue. The rest of the upper is built with tan leather and a quartet of color-popped eyelets in neon green, pink, blue, and red. An additional Jumpman logo is featured on the molded heel panel in dark beige and its two-tone foam midsole is supported by an outsole built with gum rubber under the forefoot and heel.

Inspired by the 90s, the Air Jordan 9 Retro 'University Blue' features a look similar to an Orlando Magic PE worn by Nick Anderson and Penny Hardaway. The shoe's perforated leather upper appears in white, with black contrast provided by the overlay. The branding adds color in University Blue, while Air underfoot provides cushioning. A multilingual pattern on the outsole provides traction.

Featuring the same white and black color scheme of the original 'Taxi' release from 1996 is the Air Jordan 12 Retro TD 'Royalty.' Detailed stitching is featured on the white leather upper with contrasting black mudguards in a subtle lizard texture. A metallic gold Jumpman logo can be seen on the tongue, and the lightweight foam midsole is supported by an outsole made up of herringbone-traction rubber pods under the forefoot and heel.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT White Daybreak Tropical Twist

description: Featuring a sustainable construction, the Air Jordan 12 Utility PS 'Grind' is a preschool iteration of the shoe. Built with tumbled leather, the shoe's upper appears in black, overlaid by tonal nubuck and complemented by the signature stitched lines. Jumpman branding in Bright Crimson highlights the ballistic mesh tongue, while underfoot, a phylon midsole provides cushioning. The rubber outsole incorporates 3% Nike Grind, made up of recycled scraps from factory floors and used shoes.

Celebrating the commercial holiday is the Air Jordan Retro Low 'Singles Day.' Its unique build features an upper with a black tumbled leather vamp, black synthetic suede paneling, and pale green leather overlays enlivened with geometric stitch detailing. The latter component has a glow-in-the-dark finish on the medial side, with the luminescent properties on the opposite side printed vertically and displaying 'Air Jordan 0023' and '1111 Low.' Matching green accents are featured on the embroidered Jumpman, which sits on the tongue and the 13's signature panther paw outsole, also featuring a glow-in-the-dark treatment.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'University Gold' is a grade-school shoe that draws from a Gary Payton PE from 2003. Built with black tumbled leather, the upper includes tonal radiating stitching. The basketball-textured mudguard highlights the look in University Gold, matched by the tooling underfoot. Air in the heel provides cushioning, while a midsole plate is included for stability.

Also known as the 'Lightbulb,' the Wmns Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Multi-Color' features a mixed-material build and a series of vibrant hues. The shoe's upper sports a white leather base, with patent leather on the Swoosh and eyestay and suede on the toe and heel. The collar flap and forefoot overlay are instead built with nubuck, while encapsulated Air in the midsole provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro PS 'Carmine' 2021 is a preschool iteration of a shoe that brings back an OG colorway. Released in February 2021, the shoe's upper is built with a nubuck base, finished in Carmine and overlaid by white leather. Black contrast marks the open-hole tongue and heel pull-loop, while underfoot, this model forgoes the usual visible Air of its full-size counterpart.

Originally released in 2001, the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low PS 'Bright Citrus' brings back a vibrant two-tone look two decades later. Appearing here in preschool sizes, the shoe's upper features a white leather construction, with a tonal patent leather overlay maintaining a signature element of the silhouette. The branding adds Bright Citrus to the look, with the same hue marking the rubber outsole, which provides traction. A phylon midsole is included for cushioning.

Iconic French soccer club Paris Saint-Germain teamed up with Jordan brand to create the Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Iron Grey.' The shoe's nubuck upper is finished in black and Iron Grey, with Infrared 23 accents on the Jumpman branding, lace toggle and heel pull-tab. The heel sports a hybrid logo, with 'Paname' appearing on the flag near the ankle. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

Inspired by a McDonald's commercial from 1993 in which Michael Jordan competed against Larry Bird in a game of HORSE, the Air Jordan 1 Low SE 'Nothing But Net' features a vibrant look. The shoe's black and white leather base is overlaid by textile sporting a geometric print that highlights the design. Underfoot, Air in the midsole provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 5 OG 'Metallic' 2016 brings back an OG colorway from 1990. Featuring the same black nubuck upper with a 3M reflective tongue, Fire Red accents emerge on the branding and lace lock, with metallic silver on the shark tooth detailing. Air in the heel provides cushioning, while the outsole includes icy blue translucent sections. This 2016 release was the fourth retro of the shoe.

shoeName: Jordan Delta 2 White Black Tan Infrared
description: The debut colorway of the silhouette, the Jordan Delta 2 'Thermo White' released in May 2021. Featuring a layered construction, the shoe's upper is built with a mix of semitranslucent textile and suede, supported by a TPU frame designed for lateral stability. The neutral look is highlighted by Flash Crimson throughout, while underfoot, a React foam midsole is included for cushioning. The outsole incorporates rubber pods that offer traction in high-wear areas.

The Air Jordan 1 Low SE 'Laser Blue' brings a mixed-material build to go along with its vibrant colorway. Built with a leather base, the black and white look is highlighted by Laser Blue perforated suede on the collar and heel. More Laser Blue marks the laces, while underfoot, the white Air midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a final Laser Blue hit on the concentric outsole.

Calling to mind the Air Jordan 11's OG colorway, the Jordan MA2 'Concord' emerges with a classic two-tone look. Built with a textile base, the shoe's upper appears in white, overlaid by black patent leather on the forefoot and heel. The ergonomic tongue includes a pull-loop for easy on and off, while underfoot, a sculpted foam midsole with a larger Max Air unit in the heel provides cushioning. An icy trasnlucent rubber outsole, sporting a Court Purple Jumpman, provides traction.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Metallic Pack - University Red' released as part of the three-shoe Metallic Pack. The shoe's upper is built with white leather, with tonal netting on the quarter panel and vamp. The eyelets accent the look in metallic University Red, with the color also accenting the tongue, branding and visbile Max Air unit in the heel of the midsole.

The Air Jordan 1 Low 'Shattered Backboard' delivers a chopped down version of the massively popular colorway of the sneaker that started it all. Like its predecessor, this low-top edition features a blend of white, black and orange on the upper, built with leather and nubuck instead of the all-leather construction of the high-top. Branding elements include a Jumpman on the tongue and the Wings logo on the heel.

shoeName: Jordan 3 Retro Tinker Black Cement Gold
description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro Tinker SP 'Black Cement' puts an elevated build on its classic construction. The shoe's upper is built with a mix of suede and leather, finished in black and Cement Grey, with a stylized Swoosh on the quarter panel. Reflective detailing appears on the Swoosh and perforated panels, with metallic gold upper eyelets accenting the look. Underfoot, a visible Air unit in the heel provides cushioning, giving way to a rubber outsole for traction.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro SP 'Michigan' gives the nod to the Michigan Wolverines. Released in August 2019, the shoe features a nubuck upper finished in Amarillo, supported by the classic TPU mesh inserts at the midfoot. The tongue, eyelets and collar lining emerge in College Navy to complete the team look, while a toggle lacing system supports the fit. A retro tag is stitched onto the heel, while underfoot, the midsole incorporates both colors as well as the usual shark tooth detailing, with a visible Air unit providing cushioning.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Trophy Room Chicago
description: The Trophy Room x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP 'Chicago' was limited to just 12,000 pairs. Inspired by 'the freezeout,' in which a rookie Michael Jordan was reportedly denied the ball by his veteran teammates at the 1985 NBA All-Star Game, the shoe emerges with a frozen finish throughout its construction. Designed by Marcus Jordan's sneaker boutique, the shoe's upper is built with leather, finished in white, black and Varsity Red, with the lateral heel sporting Michael Jordan's signature. Underfoot, an off-white Air midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a translucent rubber outsole with a concentric pattern for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid White Black Cyber Pink
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Cyber Active Fuchsia' emerges with a key element borrowed from the Air Jordan 11. Namely, the shoe's white leather upper is overlaid by patent leather in black. The Swoosh also sports patent leather, finished in a mismatched mix of Cyber and blue, while Active Fuchsia marks the collar and heel, made with further patent leather. Underfoot, the Air midsole gives way to a concentric rubber outsole for traction.

Placing a new palette on a classic silhouette, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Game Royal' keeps the iconic color-blocked aesthetic of the ‘Chicago’ variant but swaps red for Game Royal blue. The sneaker keeps its Summit White side panel and toe box, along with its black Swoosh and Wings logo.

The Off-White x Air Jordan 5 Retro SP TD 'Sail' released as part of a collaboration with Virgil Abloh's luxury streetwear brand. A toddlers' shoe, the upper is built with stitched textile, finished in Sail and Muslin and highlighted by '23' on the heel. A zip-tie hang-tag and Helvetica text on the medial side bring signature Abloh touches to the look, while the midfoot, collar and left tongue include circular cutouts. Underfoot, a pre-yellowed translucent rubber outsole provides traction.

In 2001, the Air Jordan 11 received a new colorway: Cool Grey. The retro-inspired low-top boasts a light grey nubuck upper and dark grey patent leather overlays, and is completed with white laces, a white midsole, and blue translucent outsole.

Made for older kids is the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Houndstooth.' It gives the retro silhouette a sartorial redesign highlighted by a white leather upper with textile overlays in a grey houndstooth print. The checked pattern makes a repeat appearance on the padded tongue, lined in lavender textile and accented with a matching Jumpman on the exterior side. It also includes metallic silver lace jewels and a silver badge on the lateral collar marked with Jumpman and '23' branding. It's built on a black and white foam midsole, supported by a lavender panther-paw outsole with black herringbone-traction rubber pods.

Released to celebrate the Chinese commercial holiday, the Wmns Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Singles Day' emerges with unique accents on its neutral construction. Built primarily with textile, the upper sports a tonal floral and basketball print throughout. A woven lace shield offers the only contrasting color, with a metallic gold Jumpman hanging off of the element. Underfoot, the midsole includes visible Air in the heel to provide cushioning.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Court Purple’ features an all-leather construction, executed with the same color-blocking seen on AJ1 models like the ‘Shattered Backboard’ and ‘Bred Toe.’ Here, the toe box, heel, and wings are finished in Court Purple, while a classic white quarter panel is overlaid with a contrasting black Swoosh. The purple Nike tag on the black nylon tongue designates the shoe's ‘OG’ status.

shoeName: Jordan 13 Retro Carmelo Anthony Class Of 2002 (B-Grade)
description: The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Melo Class of 2002’ hails Carmelo Anthony’s high school alma mater, the national basketball powerhouse Oak Hill Academy. The sneaker’s upper, a mix of nylon, leather, and suede, is finished in black, University Gold, and University Red in honor of the school’s colors. Inside, the right shoe sockliner is printed with ‘Class of 2002,’ while the left displays Melo’s personal logo. This Air Jordan 13 Retro is a Nike Factory B-Grade with minor cosmetic flaws.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Milan' released as part of the three-shoe City Pack. Inspired by the Italy's fashion capital, the shoe's pastel colorway is drawn from the city's gothic architecture. The overlays sport varying textures, while a leather MLN hang-tag completes the thematic look. The classic tooling includes Air in the heel of the midsole.

A surprise release on the SNKRS app in June 2019, the Air Jordan 4 Retro NRG 'Raptors - Drake Signature' gives the nod to one of Toronto's biggest celebrity fans. Featuring the same colorway as the first 'Raptors' model, the standout feature is the tongue patch, which includes a purple Jumpman and Drake's signature. The upper is built with black nubuck, while University Red and Court Purple throughout complete the team look.

A hybrid silhouette drawing from past Jordan models, the Jordan Spizike 270 Boot 'Dark Cinder' emerges with a subdued colorway. Built with suede, the shoe's upper appears in Dark Cinder, supported by mesh on the quarter panel and overlaid by elephant print on the toe and heel. Underfoot, the black tooling includes a 270 Max Air unit to provide cushioning, giving way to an outsole with a prominent traction pattern for off-road grip.

The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Mocha’ 2018 resurrects the unique colorway initially released in 2001. The mid top retains the original construction, showcasing a white tumbled leather upper accentuated with contrasting bursts of Dark Mocha on the shoe’s recognizable elephant-print overlays. The brown tone also emerges on the outsole and Jumpman branding emblems that decorate the tongue and heel panel.

shoeName: Jordan 3 Retro SE-T CO JP Fire Red Denim
description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro SE-T 'Fire Red' Japan Exclusive released exclusively in Japan. Built with tumbled leather, the upper appears in white, with raw denim making up the elephant-print overlays, inspired by Japanese denim. Fire Red highlights the look throughout, while the translucent heel overlay sports 'Nike' in Japanese characters. Underfoot, visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

Introduced in January 2019, the Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Laser’ commemorates the iconic silhouette’s 30th anniversary. Laser-etched designs return on this iteration, which features the adornments in subdued tonal style on a full-grain black leather upper. Eye-catching white contrasts appear on the Jumpman emblems that decorate the heel and tongue tag, while a gum rubber outsole promises superior traction.
