The Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Metallic Pack - Total Orange' emerges with an elevated two-tone look on its classic basketball construction. Built with leather, the upper appears primarily in white, including on the signature wings and mesh inserts. The eyelets accent the look in metallic Total Orange, with more Total Orange on the branding, tongue lining and Air unit in the heel of the midsole.

Part of the three-shoe City Pack, the Air Jordan 1 Low 'Paris' released exclusively in Europe. Drawing from the French capital, the shoe's simple colorway is inspired by the city's blue skies and sandstone buildings. Built with leather, suede and textile, the upper is supported underfoot by Air in the midsole and a concentric outsole.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Game Royal' dropped September 2019 in a familiar two-tone design that recalls the silhouette’s legendary ‘Flu Game’ colorway. Instead of Varsity Red, this pair sports Game Royal on the forefoot overlays and rubber outsole to contrast the sneaker’s black leather upper. The kicks are finished with Zoom Air cushioning, a first for the Jordan franchise when the 12 debuted in 1996.

The Air Jordan 1 Low GS 'Black Very Berry' is a shoe built for older kids that dresses the classic silhouette in a familiar color palette. The all-leather upper combines a black base with contrasting scarlet overlays and a solid white Swoosh. A retro Wings logo is stamped on the heel and a red Jumpman icon is embroidered on the black nylon tongue. The low-top is built on a traditional rubber cupsole with Air-sole cushioning encapsulated in a foam wedge.

Releasing in January 2015, the Air Jordan 4 Retro LS ‘Legend Blue’ brings back a colorway from 1999. A remastered version of the Air Jordan 4 ‘Columbia,’ the shoe’s white tumbled leather upper features two different shades of blue. Hits of Midnight Navy appear on most of the 4’s signature features, including the eyelets and Air-infused midsole, while the brighter Legend Blue appears on the Jumpman logos.

Part of the Rivals Pack, the Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Lakers' gives the nod to the first team that Michael Jordan beat in the NBA Finals. The classic basketball shoe sports a white base, including on the quilted overlays, with Court Purple suede on the heel and midfoot. More Court Purple emerges on the midsole, while underfoot, the herringbone outsole includes hits of University Gold to complete the team look.

A grade-school shoe, the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'Cool Grey' 2019 released as part of the 30th anniversary of the silhouette. The shoe's leather and synthetic upper appears in Cool Grey, with Dark Charcoal on the signature eyelets. Flight branding marks the tongue tag, while underfoot, the contrasting white midsole sports visible Air in the heel for cushioning. A black rubber outsole with a herringbone pattern provides traction.

Inspired by the Air Jordan 1 Metallic Pack, the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'Purple Metallic' brings an elevated two-tone look to grade-school sizes. The shoe's upper is built with white leather, highlighted by hits of metallic Court Purple on the eyelets, with more Court Purple on the tongue and branding. Mesh inserts emerge at the quarter panel and vamp, while underfoot, the white midsole sports visbile Air in the heel for cushioning.

With throwback flair, the Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Knicks Rivals' flaunts a palette influenced by a team Michael Jordan and the Chicago Bulls had to battle for Eastern Conference victory, the New York Knicks. The AJ3 was the first of countless Air Jordans designed by Tinker Hatfield and featured the debut of the iconic Jumpman emblem on the tongue. This 'Knicks Rivals' offering, issued in September 2019, retains the original profile with a white textured leather upper, elephant print on the toe cap and heel, Old Royal and University Orange color splashes, and a visible Nike Air unit.

The Air Jordan 9 Retro OG 'Space Jam' 2016 released to help celebrate the 20th anniversary of Space Jam. The look recreates the shoes that were taken from Michael Jordan's house by Daffy Duck and Bugs Bunny in the film, which Jordan later wore during the film's training montage. The black and white design is accented by True Red on the branding, most notably on the heel.

Inspired by handmade craftsmanship, the Jordan Delta Breathe 'Guava Ice' emerges with a pastel look on its lifestyle construction. The shoe's upper is built with semitranslucent textile, overlaid by suede on the heel overlay and sporting tongue and heel pull-loops for easy on and off. The hand-drawn Jumpman branding, zigzag stitching and exposed-foam collar all work to contribute to a deconstructed aesthetic, while underfoot, full-length Nike React in the midsole provides cushioning.

One of two debut colorways of the silhouette, the Jordan Series.01 'Anthracite' is a lifestyle shoe. Also known as the 'Dear Mike,' the shoe pays tribute to a young Michael Jordan, whose competitive fire was stoked by his older brother Larry. As a result, 'Dear Mike' appears on the Jumpman-branded tongue tag, with 'Swing for the Fences' on the left insole. Built with suede and leather, the shoe's upper appears in black, contrasted underfoot by the white rubber midsole. The white rubber outsole sports '45/2,' a nod to Jordan's selection of 23 as a jersey number because of his belief that if he was half as good as Larry, who wore 45, he'd be on the path to success.

Part of Jordan Brand's 2019 holiday collection, the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Dark Grey' emerges with a largely nuetral look. The shoe's nubuck and leather upper appears in white, with grey on the signature basketball-textured mudguard. Gym Red Jumpman branding brings the only color to the look, while underfoot, a midsole plate and herringbone outsole support the fit.

shoeName: Jordan 11 Retro Low IE Space Jam
description: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low IE 'Space Jam' updates a classic colorway while giving the nod to Space Jam. Released in July 2019, the shoe's upper is built primarily with mesh and finished in black, overlaid by black patent leather on the mudguard and smooth leather on the toe. A Concord Jumpman accents the tongue, while underfoot, a white Air midsole provides cushioning, giving way to an icy translucent rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Carmine' 2014 brings back one of the Air Jordan 6's OG colorways. The signature perforated upper features white overlays highlighted by Carmine underlays, with the bright red also on the tongue, lace lock, heel and branding. A visible Air unit in the midsole provides cushioning, and the partially translucent outsole reveals another hit of Carmine underfoot.

The 2013 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Taxi’ brings back the iconic OG colorway worn by Michael Jordan during the 1996-97 NBA season. The design is faithful to the original, featuring a stitched white leather upper with metallic gold eyelets and textured black leather overlays. Contrasting pops of yellow appear on the heel loop and carbon fiber shank plate underfoot.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Patent Black White Gold
description: Boasting familiar design ingredients from previously released Air Jordan 1s, the Air Jordan 1 Mid Patent ‘Black Gold’ features patent leather and metallic gold accents. The first emerges on the overlays that stand out against a classic white leather base. The second makes its appearance on the Swoosh and branding components that deck out the shoe’s collar, tongue tag, and sockliner.

The Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Gym Red’ flaunts an eye-catching rendition of Tinker Hatfield’s 1996 design. The entirety of the mid-top silhouette is dramatically dipped in red, including the rubber tooling and herringbone tread outsole. Contrasting accents of black burst throughout the shoe’s branding elements and sockliner. While the all-red finish presents a revolutionary redesign of the vintage silhouette, the performance benefits stay true to the original, evidenced by full-length Zoom Air that extends from heel to toe.

shoeName: Jordan 4 Retro Olivia Kim No Cover (W)
description: The Olivia Kim x women’s Air Jordan 4 Retro 'No Cover' dropped in 2019 as part of a retro footwear collection conceived by Nordstrom’s VP of Creative Projects. As Olivia came of age in the ‘90s, it’s no surprise that the assortment features an Air Jordan 4. Inspired by MJ’s ‘Black Cat’ nickname, the sneaker boasts an all-black calf hair upper, complete with Nike Air branding on the heel.

The 2016 grade-school edition of the Air Jordan 11 Retro ‘Space Jam’ marks the 20th anniversary of the classic film of the same name. The shoe itself brings back a fan-favorite colorway, which debuted on the feet of Michael Jordan during the 1995 Eastern Conference Semifinals. This pair is true to the original, an all-black upper in ballistic mesh and patent leather. ‘45’ is the finishing touch on the heel tab.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High COJP Midnight Navy (PS)
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High CO.JP PS 'Midnight Navy' is a preschool shoe. Bringing back a 2001 colorway that was a Japan-exclusive, the shoe features a white leather base overlaid by Midnight Navy nubuck, highlighted by metallic silver on the Swoosh and 'Wings' branding. Rather than a Jumpman, the tongue includes embroidered Nike branding, while the CO.JP sockliner gives the nod to the OG release.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Laney' 2013 gives the nod to Michael Jordan's high school. Originally released in 2000, the shoe's white leather upper is accented by hits of Royal Blue and Varsity Maize to complete the E.A. Laney High School look. Visible Air in the heel and an icy blue translucent outsole maintain the signature Jordan 5 tooling.

The Sneakersnstuff x Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Past, Present, Future' released to celebrate 20 years of the Swedish retailer's first store. Part of a three-shoe collection, the off-white leather and grey distressed nubuck upper is drawn from Sneakersnstuff's first location. Gym Red accents the look, while Air in the heel provides cushioning.

Also known as the 'Multi Snakeskin,' the Wmns Air Jordan 1 Low 'Coachella' released in April 2020. Built with a black tumbled leather base, the upper is highlighted by a series of colorful snakeksin overlays. Metallic gold detailing accents the side wall, while underfoot, a white midsole provides cushioning and contrast.

The Air Jordan 7 Retro 30th ‘Barcelona Nights’ celebrates the silhouette’s historic significance, as the shoe was worn by MJ at the ’92 Summer Olympics as a member of the vaunted Dream Team. The venue for those games was Barcelona, and the picturesque view of the city at night is the inspiration for this special-edition colorway, highlighted by bright accents on a black nubuck and leather upper.

The 2011 reissue of the Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘White Cement’ brings back the OG colorway of the iconic silhouette that introduced elephant print, visible Air cushioning and the Jumpman logo to the Jordan franchise. Constructed from white tumbled leather with Fire Red accents, the mid-top is finished with a second Jumpman hit on the heel panel, replacing the OG Nike Air wordmark.

An April 2019 release, the Air Jordan 14 Retro 'Candy Cane' 2019 is the second retro of the festive colorway. The shoe's leather upper includes tumbled and smooth finishes as well as perforations for breathability, while Varsity Red accents emerge on the tongue, heel and midsole. Zoom Air provides cushioning, with a shank plate for stability, giving way to an outsole with a herringbone traction pattern.

The women’s Air Jordan 11 Retro ‘Olive Lux’ upgrades the classic silhouette with a premium redesign, highlighted by a mudguard that ditches patent leather for suede, burnished with a distinctive metallic sheen. The 11’s ballistic mesh construction is also replaced with olive suede, while a metallic Jumpman accents the lateral collar. A chic white midsole is strengthened by a translucent gum rubber outsole underfoot.

A collaboration between Nike and Eric Koston, the Eric Koston x Air Jordan 1 Low SB 'Midnight Navy' brings a skateboarding touch to the classic hoops shoe. Inspired by a similiar look that released in 2001, the shoe features a suede upper in a mix of Midnight Navy and white, accented by metallic silver on the Swoosh branding. Jumpman branding emerges on the perforated toe box, while underfoot, Zoom Air in the sockliner provides cushioning.

Originally released as part of the two-shoe Thunder and Lightning pack in 2006, the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Thunder' 2012 dropped six years later. The shoe's upper is built with a black nubuck base, highlighted by Tour Yellow on the molded eyelets, quarter panel and tongue lining. Underfoot, more Tour Yellow accents the polyurethane midsole, which includes the usual visible Air in the heel for cushioning. A rubber outsole is included for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low Sail University Gold Black
description: The Air Jordan 1 Low 'University Gold' brings a vibrant look to its liefstyle construction. The shoe's low-cut upper includes a full suede build in a mix of University Gold, Sail and black, with Gym Red branding accenting the tongue. Underfoot, a white Air midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a University Gold outsole with a concentric pattern.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro GG 'Citron Tint' is a girls' shoe with a vibrant look. Built with leather, the upper appears in Citron Tint with Dynamic Yellow accents, perforated throughout for breathabilty. The tongue sports an embroidered yellow rose along with black Jumpman branding, with further floral hits on the lining and inside the tongue. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Island Green' takes on a tropical aesthetic, highlighted by Island Green accents on a white leather upper embellished with a tonal palm tree print and a 3M reflective finish. Completing the distinctive design are the silhouette’s signature flourishes, including clear lace locks, shark tooth detailing on the midsole and a translucent rubber outsole underfoot.

The Sheila Rashid x Air Jordan 1 Mid 'UNITE' is the result of a collaboration between the bespoke designer and Jordan Brand. Drawn from the 8x8 collection that featured the work of eight Chicago creatives, the shoe emerges with a split look that sports purple leather on the forefoot and grey hairy suede on the quarter panel and heel. The midsole underfoot maintains the two-tone look.

Released in April 2014, the Air Jordan 9 Retro 'Barons' honors Michael Jordan's brief stint with the Birmingham Barons. The colorway of white, black, and Wolf Grey features pinstripe detailing on the heel collar, a 3M heel tab, and his jersey #45 on the heel.

The 1996 NBA All-Star Game was Michael Jordan's first in three years, and the Air Jordan 11 BG Retro ‘Legend’ Blue from December 2014 is based on the Air Jordan 11 ‘Columbia’ that Jordan wore in that game. The University of North Carolina-style colorway features Legend Blue accents throughout, most notably on the panther’s paw outsole.

In honor of the NBA All-Star weekend, Jordan Brand teamed up with Toronto-based OVO label to produce a distinctive shoe for Drake. The OVO x Air Jordan 8 Retro ' White ' features an upper white suede and tumbled leather with red accents on the tongue's Jumpman logo, metallic gold accents on the toe box, heel pull tabs, and a midfoot paintbrush pattern. The high top also features an ankle strap, a black rubber midsole, and OVO branding and owls all over.

A largely neutral look, the Jordan Delta 2 'Lightning' is subtly highlighted by mismatched pastel accents. The shoe's textile upper appears in white, overlaid by grey suede at the forefoot. A semitranslucent molded overlay supports the lateral side, while the left shoe includes yellow suede to accent the look, with green on the right. Underfoot, a React midsole provides cushioning, giving way to durable rubber pods on high-wear areas of the outsole.

Debuted in 1995 as part of a five-piece City Pack, the Air Jordan 10 OG in the ‘Orlando’ colorway returned to store shelves in December 2018. The build retains the OG structure, with a white tumbled leather upper accented by black contrasts on the tongue, throat, laces, and midsole. Bursts of royal blue on the collar lining and rubber outsole add the finishing touch to the Orlando Magic’s team colors.

colorway: Guava Ice/Light Bone-Brigade Blue-Light Fusion Red
description: Jordan Brand teamed up with Union LA to create the Union LA x Jordan Zoom '92 'Guava Ice' in August 2020. Drawing from a previous Air Jordan 4 collaboration, the shoe's construction draws from the Air Max 180, Air Force 5 and Air Jordan 7, with a layered build on the upper. Highlighted by hits of Brigade Blue and Light Fusion Red, a heel pull-loop provides easy on and off. Underfoot, the yellowed midsole sports visible Zoom Air in the forefoot to provide cushioning.

A girls' shoe, the Air Jordan 11 GG Heiress 'Velvet' features an elevated colorway to go with its elevated construction. The shoe emerges with a nubuck upper, overlaid by crushed velvet and finished in Night Maroon. The branding highlights the design in metallic gold, while underfoot, a full-length phylon midsole in white provides cushioning and contrast, giving way to a semitranslucent rubber outsole for traction.

The Jordan Delta 2 'White Royal' brings a clean colorway to its lifestyle running constructijon. Built with a mix of mesh, leather and suede, the shoe's upper appears in white, with a prominent heel pull-loop included for easy on and off. The tongue tag and quarter panel flag add blue to the look, with black 'Jordan' branding contrasting the side wall, while a molded TPU mudguard is included for stability. Underfoot, a React midsole provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ' Sail ' features a tone Sail rubber outsole with an off-white Sail leather upper. The design also involves branding on the tongue tab of the University Red Nike Air. The ' Sail ' fell alongside a ' Triple Black ' colorway as part of the ' Premium Essentials ' pack in June 2017.

In celebration of Will Smith’s 50th birthday, Nike released this Air Jordan 5 Retro in a nod to one of the actor’s most engaging roles: The Fresh Prince. Inspired by the laceless AJ5 model that Smith was known to wear on the set of The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air, the NRG 'Fresh Prince' seals up the eyestays entirely and wraps the high-top in a vibrant Grape Ice and New Emerald colorway. The design’s clearest tribute to the sitcom can be found on the insole, where ‘Air Jordan’ branding appears in the style of the show’s title sequence graffiti.

shoeName: Jordan Why Not .5 HTG Honor the Gift

description: The Nike Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Cavs' celebrates the 23rd anniversary of 'The Shot,' the last-second bucket of Michael Jordan over Craig Ehlo that defeated the Cleveland Cavaliers in the '89 Playoffs. With Safety Orange and Game Royal accents, the design features a black nubuck top. The sneaker fell in limited amounts in May 2012.

The Air Jordan 7 Retro 'Sweater' draws inspiration from an outfit worn by Michael Jordan at the 1992 Barcelona Summer Olympics and in a 1993 McDonald's Super Bowl commercial with Larry Bird. Also known as the 'Nothing But Net,' the 2015 release combines a vibrant graphic design with upper white leather, black, University Red, and Bright Concord tongue, heel, and outsole accents.

The Air Jordan 9 'Cool Grey' was introduced in 2002 and made a famous comeback in 2012. The shoe is made of smooth nubuck with a patent leather mudguard and matching translucent rubber outsole, dressed in complementary colors of Cool Grey and Medium Grey. White accents give contrasting touches on the heel's midsole, laces, and "23."

shoeName: Jordan 13 Retro Reverse He Got Game (GS)
Jordan Aerospace 720 Rookie of the Year
description: Drawing from an Air Jordan 1 colorway of the same name, the Jordan Aerospace 720 'Rookie of the Year' features inspiration from Michael Jordan's Rookie of the Year acceptance speech in 1985. Built with textile, the upper appears in white, with mesh on the quarter panel and synthetic leather overlays supporting the fit. Underfoot, a 720 Max Air unit provides cushioning.

Featuring a subdued look, the Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 'Easter' released in May 2021. The shoe's upper is built with a mesh base, bolstered by synthetic overlays and secured by webbing straps. A heel pull-loop offers easy on and off, while underfoot, the white foam midsole houses double-stacked Zoom Air, providing cushioning and contrast. A data-informed pattern on the decoupled rubber outsole provides traction and completes the understated look.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE Disco Metallic Silver (W)
description: The Wmns Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Disco Ball' gets its name from the gridded, silver finish throughout its construction. The reflective design continues onto the solid Swoosh, while matte silver emerges on the laces and mesh tongue. Underfoot, a white Air midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a black rubber outsole with a concentric traction pattern.

Released for Black History Month 2011, the Air Jordan 3 'Black History Month' offers a minimalist take on Michael Jordan's third signature shoe. The shoe's black upper is built with a mix of premium nubuck and leather, with metallic gold on the stitching, eyelets and branding. The traditional elephant print overlays have been replaced by laser-etched graphics, while the inside of the tongue includes 'BHM' branding.

The Air Jordan 29 ‘Pantone’ dropped in 2014 as part of the ‘Ultimate Gift of Flight’ Pack, which also included an accompanying Air Jordan 11. The performance hoops shoe features a one-piece woven upper, accented with Pantone blue accents and a stylized version of Jordan Brand’s iconic elephant print. The kicks are finished with a metallic silver midsole and an icy translucent rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid 'University Gold' emerges with a vibrant contrasting colorway. The shoe's University Gold upper is built with tumbled leather, while solid black emerges on the nylon tongue, inner lining and Swoosh branding. 'Wings' branding appears tonally on the collar, while underfoot, a white Air midsole provides cushioning. The black rubber outsole sports a concentric pattern for traction.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Green Bean' recreates the OG look with a notable addition: reflective detailing on the silver sections of the upper. The lining, tongue and shark tooth detailing are all finished in Green Bean, with another hit of the color on the Jumpman branding underfoot.

shoeName: Jordan XXXIII Metallic Silver Black All Star
description: A classic inspiration, the Air Jordan 33 ‘All Star’ commemorates the 2019 NBA All-Star Game, hosted in Michael Jordan’s home state of North Carolina. The high-performing basketball sneaker boasts a streamlined look due to a silver mesh upper overlaid with metallic silver paneling and standout black around the tongue, collar, and medial-side forefoot. The red and blue straps integrated into the shoe’s revolutionary FastFit system provide bursts of color.

Featuring the same color blocking at the 1997 'Bred,' the Air Jordan 13 Retro TD 'Hyper Royal' emerges with a more subdued look. The shoe's upper appears in a two-tone mix of black and Hyper Royal, overlaid by reflective mesh on the side wall. The collar includes the classic hologram logo, while underfoot, the tooling continues the two-tone look, with a herringbone outsole providing traction.

The 'Royal' was Michael Jordan's personal favorite OG Air Jordan 1 colorway, and the Jordan 1 Mid TD 'Royal' brings that iconic look to the football field. Repurposed as a cleat, the mid-top shoe is built with a mix of synthetic and textile, finished in black and Royal. The usual branding hits remain intact, including a 'Wings' logo on the collar, while underfoot, a contrasting white Lunarlon midsole provides cushioning. Rubber studs on the outsole in black and Royal provide traction.

shoeName: Jordan Team Elite 2 Low White Metallic Silver

description: The Air Jordan 1 Low SE GS 'Houndstooth' is a low-top made for kids. It has a black leather upper with grey houndstooth textile on the Swoosh and collar. The interior is lined with lavender-colored mesh as well as the Jumpman icon atop the tongue and stitched Wings logo on the heel overlay. The pastel hue is repeated on the high-traction rubber outsole. On the lace bed, metallic silver dubrae feature molded '23' and Wings branding.

shoeName: Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 Low Black White
